 # Restructure AGENTS.md with progressive disclosure — split into focused docs
 
-
+The project AGENTS.md is ~6800 tokens and growing. It needs progressive disclosure:
+
+1. Core AGENTS.md should be a concise overview with 'read X before doing Y' directives
+2. Detailed sections should be extracted to docs/ files
+3. Each extracted doc should be self-contained and cross-referenced
+
+Candidates for extraction:
+- Build System & Distribution → docs/build-system.md
+- How Extensions Are Loaded → docs/extension-loading.md
+- TUI Development → already has .sandpiper/docs/tui-extension-patterns.md
+- Environment Variables → docs/env-vars.md
+- Pi Extension API Pitfalls → docs/pi-api-pitfalls.md
+- CLI Development patterns → docs/cli-development.md
+
+The core AGENTS.md should focus on: repo structure, coding standards, testing, version control, task management — with pointers to detailed docs for specific topics.
+
+Also consider: should extracted docs live in docs/ (visible, part of the repo) or .sandpiper/docs/ (agent-specific)? Architectural/framework docs feel like they belong in docs/ alongside Pi's own docs.
